{"submission_id":"sub_bbc7d33d791d9ad2","run_id":"2026-06-20T15-21-02-175Z_1885472-db2432d9_ingest_meeting-doc-135381","submitted_at":"2026-06-20T16:27:45.488Z","tool_args_sha256":"sha256:bbc7d33d791d9ad27532fc5fcc1d4fba7c7e561e28d068cb9eb9e49bcb616f2a","schema_version":2,"tool_args":{"source_id":"meeting_doc_135381","observation_kind":"claim","local_observation_id":"claim_meeting_doc_135381_extension_purpose","label":"Extension purpose - continue refuse removal for NYC Transit, MTA Bus, and SIR","raw_text":"MTA Headquarters is seeking Board approval to extend the miscellaneous service contract awarded to Action Carting Environmental Services Inc to continue Refuse Removal and Recycling Services for New York City Transit, MTA Bus, and Staten Island Railway stations, yards, barns, depots, and administrative facilities for a two-year period (May 1, 2024–April 30, 2026) in the amount of $19,353,002.","payload":{"claim_text":"MTA Headquarters is seeking Board approval to extend the miscellaneous service contract awarded to Action Carting Environmental Services Inc to continue Refuse Removal and Recycling Services for New York City Transit, MTA Bus, and Staten Island Railway stations, yards, barns, depots, and administrative facilities for a two-year period (May 1, 2024–April 30, 2026) in the amount of $19,353,002."},"evidence_refs":[{"source_id":"meeting_doc_135381","evidence_id":"meeting_doc_135381#p006_c0006","source_path":"raw/sources/meeting_doc_135381/blocks.jsonl","page_number":6,"block_id":"p006_c0006","text_sha256":"sha256:cb8391afa4164ebf90cc7a88015fa5b0feef74f3dd340a1a31e7f4406af81786","text_source":"raw_text","role":"text"}]},"validation":{"state":"accepted","issues":[]}}
{"submission_id":"sub_781907f9c5a67c0a","run_id":"2026-06-20T15-21-02-175Z_1885472-db2432d9_ingest_meeting-doc-135381","submitted_at":"2026-06-20T16:34:33.716Z","tool_args_sha256":"sha256:781907f9c5a67c0ab736a4c2cc54906dd42c9a8b6d59ab786430dfc91d19ba02","schema_version":2,"tool_args":{"source_id":"meeting_doc_135381","observation_kind":"claim","local_observation_id":"claim_meeting_doc_135381_extension_reasons","label":"Extension purposes - consolidation, CWZ program, waste audit","raw_text":"The purpose of this extension is to (1) facilitate the time needed to allow the MTA's objective of consolidation of services through a category management approach that will aggregate requirements across the Agencies in common geographic regions and potentially generate cost savings associated with awarding multiple contracts based on geographical territories; (2) allow time for the NYC Commercial Waste Zone (\"CWZ\") program to fully implement; and (3) allow Project Management time to prepare and execute a third-party audit of the waste stream","payload":{"claim_text":"The purpose of this extension is to (1) facilitate the time needed to allow the MTA's objective of consolidation of services through a category management approach that will aggregate requirements across the Agencies in common geographic regions and potentially generate cost savings associated with awarding multiple contracts based on geographical territories; (2) allow time for the NYC Commercial Waste Zone program to fully implement; and (3) allow Project Management time to prepare and execute a third-party audit of the waste stream."},"evidence_refs":[{"source_id":"meeting_doc_135381","evidence_id":"meeting_doc_135381#p006_c0008","source_path":"raw/sources/meeting_doc_135381/blocks.jsonl","page_number":6,"block_id":"p006_c0008","text_sha256":"sha256:c1ff98a34b43ad4d322ba50252dc9b19a45cf12ecb7e0bf912069f416085809b","text_source":"raw_text","role":"text"}]},"validation":{"state":"accepted","issues":[]}}
{"submission_id":"sub_fe258a9c8d994be5","run_id":"2026-06-20T15-21-02-175Z_1885472-db2432d9_ingest_meeting-doc-135381","submitted_at":"2026-06-20T16:35:04.355Z","tool_args_sha256":"sha256:fe258a9c8d994be5ff1302a04f979915612aef549ada1d1b757f95db970828f4","schema_version":2,"tool_args":{"source_id":"meeting_doc_135381","observation_kind":"claim","local_observation_id":"claim_meeting_doc_135381_zero_increases","label":"Zero percent increases negotiated for certain line items","raw_text":"MTA Procurement was able to negotiate and maintain zero percent increases for the following line items: (1) as-needed hauling and disposal of track debris; (2) office trailers and Conex Boxes; (3) bulk subway station refuse; (4) recyclables; (5) document destruction; (6) transfer station charges for Sunday operations; and (7) emergency services.","payload":{"claim_text":"MTA Procurement was able to negotiate and maintain zero percent increases for the following line items: (1) as-needed hauling and disposal of track debris; (2) office trailers and Conex Boxes; (3) bulk subway station refuse; (4) recyclables; (5) document destruction; (6) transfer station charges for Sunday operations; and (7) emergency services."},"evidence_refs":[{"source_id":"meeting_doc_135381","evidence_id":"meeting_doc_135381#p006_c0010","source_path":"raw/sources/meeting_doc_135381/blocks.jsonl","page_number":6,"block_id":"p006_c0010","text_sha256":"sha256:7d2873d48a346ed8a33015896dc9740bda6294240cd4e594fbc33f88da51ab05","text_source":"raw_text","role":"text"}]},"validation":{"state":"accepted","issues":[]}}
{"submission_id":"sub_4dcc64dd7273ffe8","run_id":"2026-06-20T15-21-02-175Z_1885472-db2432d9_ingest_meeting-doc-135381","submitted_at":"2026-06-20T16:35:29.327Z","tool_args_sha256":"sha256:4dcc64dd7273ffe8cb86871751160d3c1911396abcde17dd7b4654b6873e1471","schema_version":2,"tool_args":{"source_id":"meeting_doc_135381","observation_kind":"claim","local_observation_id":"claim_meeting_doc_135381_cwz_truck_reduction","label":"CWZ program - intended to reduce truck traffic by 50%","raw_text":"This approach is intended to reduce truck traffic associated with commercial waste collection by 50 percent, eliminating millions of heavy-duty truck miles from NY City streets each year while strengthening service standards and allowing for customer choice.","payload":{"claim_text":"This approach is intended to reduce truck traffic associated with commercial waste collection by 50 percent, eliminating millions of heavy-duty truck miles from NY City streets each year while strengthening service standards and allowing for customer choice."},"evidence_refs":[{"source_id":"meeting_doc_135381","evidence_id":"meeting_doc_135381#p006_c0009","source_path":"raw/sources/meeting_doc_135381/blocks.jsonl","page_number":6,"block_id":"p006_c0009","text_sha256":"sha256:d1ed0c4e623dcd6a13ca5811de4bb2bfbcdcd37f06da34c4fca7a0eaa5e2ef4e","text_source":"raw_text","role":"text"}]},"validation":{"state":"accepted","issues":[]}}
{"submission_id":"sub_bf1290bd1357b3fc","run_id":"2026-06-20T15-21-02-175Z_1885472-db2432d9_ingest_meeting-doc-135381","submitted_at":"2026-06-20T16:35:53.377Z","tool_args_sha256":"sha256:bf1290bd1357b3fc7ae182fde89b12d2f1fc84274ffe9d57ef1437173f833cfc","schema_version":2,"tool_args":{"source_id":"meeting_doc_135381","observation_kind":"claim","local_observation_id":"claim_meeting_doc_135381_ppi_increases","label":"Extension pricing increased per PPI escalation","raw_text":"Due to industry-wide regulated increases, extension pricing for the following contract line items were increased in line with Producer Price Index escalation: (1) pickup and disposal of compacted/uncompacted subway/non-subway refuse, (2) disposal of construction and demolition debris, and (3) hauling of open-top containers. Pricing will remain firm for the two-year extension period.","payload":{"claim_text":"Due to industry-wide regulated increases, extension pricing for the following contract line items were increased in line with Producer Price Index escalation: (1) pickup and disposal of compacted/uncompacted subway/non-subway refuse, (2) disposal of construction and demolition debris, and (3) hauling of open-top containers. Pricing will remain firm for the two-year extension period."},"evidence_refs":[{"source_id":"meeting_doc_135381","evidence_id":"meeting_doc_135381#p006_c0010","source_path":"raw/sources/meeting_doc_135381/blocks.jsonl","page_number":6,"block_id":"p006_c0010","text_sha256":"sha256:7d2873d48a346ed8a33015896dc9740bda6294240cd4e594fbc33f88da51ab05","text_source":"raw_text","role":"text"}]},"validation":{"state":"accepted","issues":[]}}
{"submission_id":"sub_d9c3b3a2d156389e","run_id":"2026-06-20T15-21-02-175Z_1885472-db2432d9_ingest_meeting-doc-135381","submitted_at":"2026-06-20T16:36:20.007Z","tool_args_sha256":"sha256:d9c3b3a2d156389e6d30533663c690ee8a22b4b881733ac465189b521dea5d3e","schema_version":2,"tool_args":{"source_id":"meeting_doc_135381","observation_kind":"claim","local_observation_id":"claim_meeting_doc_135381_cwz_exemption","label":"MTA exempt from CWZ program; B&T status under review","raw_text":"While it has been determined that the MTA is exempt from this program 1 , the full impact is unknown at this time as its implementation is not expected to be completed until the end of 2024. This could affect the quantity and quality of vendors available to contract with the MTA, which may influence the procurement approach.","payload":{"claim_text":"While it has been determined that the MTA is exempt from this program, the full impact is unknown at this time as its implementation is not expected to be completed until the end of 2024. The exemption status of B&T is currently under review."},"evidence_refs":[{"source_id":"meeting_doc_135381","evidence_id":"meeting_doc_135381#p006_c0012","source_path":"raw/sources/meeting_doc_135381/blocks.jsonl","page_number":6,"block_id":"p006_c0012","text_sha256":"sha256:1a9ae804707135c05cacb3b06a13dc87daecd91795eab64aa64ae8320d86e9d1","text_source":"raw_text","role":"footnote"},{"source_id":"meeting_doc_135381","evidence_id":"meeting_doc_135381#p006_c0009","source_path":"raw/sources/meeting_doc_135381/blocks.jsonl","page_number":6,"block_id":"p006_c0009","text_sha256":"sha256:d1ed0c4e623dcd6a13ca5811de4bb2bfbcdcd37f06da34c4fca7a0eaa5e2ef4e","text_source":"raw_text","role":"text"}]},"validation":{"state":"accepted","issues":[]}}
{"submission_id":"sub_980808544be83644","run_id":"2026-06-20T15-21-02-175Z_1885472-db2432d9_ingest_meeting-doc-135381","submitted_at":"2026-06-20T16:36:47.671Z","tool_args_sha256":"sha256:980808544be83644c0e488b25a505ac40156b4f1fb1541e2d1bd796fc238bf78","schema_version":2,"tool_args":{"source_id":"meeting_doc_135381","observation_kind":"claim","local_observation_id":"claim_meeting_doc_135381_base_contract_history","label":"Base contract awarded Feb 2019, one prior change order","raw_text":"The base contract was awarded in February 2019 for $39,170,973. To date, there has been one change order to increase the contract by $995,000 (from $39,170,973 to $40,165,973) and extend the period of performance by three months (February 1, 2024–April 30, 2024).","payload":{"claim_text":"The base contract was awarded in February 2019 for $39,170,973. To date, there has been one change order to increase the contract by $995,000 (from $39,170,973 to $40,165,973) and extend the period of performance by three months (February 1, 2024–April 30, 2024)."},"evidence_refs":[{"source_id":"meeting_doc_135381","evidence_id":"meeting_doc_135381#p006_c0007","source_path":"raw/sources/meeting_doc_135381/blocks.jsonl","page_number":6,"block_id":"p006_c0007","text_sha256":"sha256:db4e9344fccc791d1fb09be94705765972ddd7e79796d4329a530a3b72d0c0bf","text_source":"raw_text","role":"text"}]},"validation":{"state":"accepted","issues":[]}}
